  "Message": "feat(stripe): webhook handler + ngrok tunnel for Epic Fury 2026\n\nRouter: backend/routers/stripe_webhook.py\n- POST /api/stripe/webhook (wired into main.py via include_router)\n- Raw request.body() before JSON parsing — required for Stripe HMAC-SHA256 [1]\n- Fail-closed: missing/malformed STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET returns 500\n- Idempotency guard: duplicate event_id acknowledged without reprocessing [2]\n- Always 2xx for unhandled event types — prevents 72-hr retry storms [3]\n- _f() helper: safe field access on stripe\u003e=5 StripeObject + plain dicts\n- 5 event handlers (TODO stubs for Epic Fury business logic):\n    checkout.session.completed, invoice.paid, invoice.payment_failed,\n    customer.subscription.updated, customer.subscription.deleted\n\nTunnel: scripts/start_ngrok_tunnel.sh\n- Static domain: portfolio-hoch-agent-swarm.ngrok-free.dev (free, permanent)\n- Webhook URL: https://portfolio-hoch-agent-swarm.ngrok-free.dev/api/stripe/webhook\n- Run this to expose localhost:8000 to Stripe during development\n\nTests: 10 passing (all event types, unknown type, idempotency, fail-closed)\n\n[1] https://docs.stripe.com/webhooks#verify-official-libraries\n[2] https://docs.stripe.com/webhooks#handle-duplicate-events\n[3] https://docs.stripe.com/webhooks#best-practices",
  "Tags": [],
  "Fingerprint": "45f6e2714c3df8427e978502f5e1f693849acacd:tests/unit/test_stripe_webhook.py:generic-api-key:16"
 },
